PREQUEST FOR PROPOSAL (RFP)
1. Background & Objective
The Forest Department, Government of Telangana, proposes to implement T-FOMS
to digitize forest offense reporting, enhance transparency, and improve monitoring
and decision-making through technology.
2. Scope of Work
The scope includes design, development, testing, deployment, training, and
maintenance of a mobile application and web portal with offline data capture, geo-
tagging, secure evidence management, dashboards and MIS reports.
3. Consultation & Review Meetings
The selected bidder shall conduct a minimum of two (2) review meetings, either
online or offline, with departmental officers during the development phase for
finalization of software requirements, workflows and outputs. Additional meetings
may be conducted if required without extra cost.
Project Duration & Completion Timeline:
The successful bidder shall complete the design, development, testing and deployment
of the T-FOMS system and achieve Go-Live within 6 0 (SIXTY) days from the date of
signing of the agreement.
Post Go-Live, the bidder shall provide comprehensive technical support and
handholding for a minimum period of three (3) months at no additional cost to the
Department.
4. Post-Implementation Support
The bidder shall provide comprehensive technical support, bug fixes and handholding
for a minimum period of three (3) months after Go-Live of the system, at no
additional cost to the Department.
5. Eligibility Criteria
Bidders shall be Companies / LLPs / DPIIT-recognized Startups / Government
entities with experience in IT systems, mobile applications or enterprise software
solutions.
6. Evaluation Methodology
Evaluation shall be carried out under QCBS method with 70% weightage to Technical
Bid and 30% weightage to Financial Bid.
7. Payment Schedule
Payments shall be released as follows: 20% on signing of agreement, 40% on
successful User Acceptance Testing (UAT), and 40% on Go-Live and final
acceptance.
