SCOPE OF WORK (SoW)
2.1 Project Overview
The Department seeks t o implement T-FOMS (Telangana Forest Offense Management
System), à "Central Nervous System" for forest protection modeled after CCTNS. The
system must digitize the "First Response" workflow.
2.2 Functional Requirements
A. Mobile Application ("The Digital Lathi")
• Target User: Forest Guards/Beat Officers.
• Platform: Android (Native/Flutter).
• Mandatory Features:
1 . Offline "Store-and-Forward" Architecture: App must function i n deep
forest areas without internet and auto-sync when connectivity is restored.
2. Voice-to-Text AI: Integrated NLP module to convert spoken incident
details into structured text for Preliminary Offense Reports (POR).
3. Geo-Fenced Evidence: Capture of GPS coordinates (Lat/Long) and
timestamp is mandatory for all reports.
4. Restricted Media Upload: Photos/Videos must be captured live via the app
camera only (gallery upload disabled) to ensure evidence integrity.
5. Biometric Login: Multi-factor authentication using fingerprint/Face ID.
B . Admin Command Portal ("The HQ")
• Target User: DFOs, Rangers, PCCF.
• Platform: Web-based (ReactS).
• Mandatory Features:
1 . Live Dashboard: Kanban-style visualization o f case status (Reported →
Verified → Charge Sheet → Closed).
2. Automated PDF Generation: One-click generation o f Seizure Lists and
PORs i n official government formats.
3. GIS Heatmaps: Visualization of offense hotspots o n a map.
2.3 Technical Architecture Requirements
• Backend: Java Spring Boot (Required for enterprise security).
• Database: PostgreSQL + PostGIS (For geospatial data).
• nfrastructure: Docker/Kubernetes compatible
•Xi Service: Python-based microservice for Voice-to- Text processing.
